org.graalvm.nativeimage

Interface Isolates.ProtectionDomain

  • Enclosing class:
    Isolates

    public static interface Isolates.ProtectionDomain
    Identifies a protection domain for an isolate. A protection domain may be used by a MemoryProtectionKeyProvider in connection with underlying MMU hardware such as Memory Protection Keys.
    Since:
    22.1

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static Isolates.ProtectionDomain NEW_DOMAIN
      Creates a new protection domain if passed to the Isolates.CreateIsolateParameters.Builder.
      static Isolates.ProtectionDomain NO_DOMAIN
      Do not use a protection domain.
